  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To Provide Food &amp; Hygiene Support to Covid Impacted Manual Scavengers Households</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supply of cooked food to Covid impacted HH will improve the nutrition and immunity of the individuals in fighting the Covid.  Grocery support to HH also ensure food security to entire family who are restricted to venture out.  Supply of basic medication based on submission of prescription would help in containing the fever and infection.  SHG leaders will be able to monitor the Covid spread within the community using the oximeter and thermometer will help in isolation of individuals showing symptoms at early stage.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project intervention to cover Manual scavengers live in big cities of Delhi, Ranch, Lucknow and Patna.  The activities include providing cooked food three times a day to 750 Covid impacted HH for 15 days.  1000HH to receive dry ration if any one the family members is infected. 2500 HH also to receive essential medicines, 2 units of three layered masks, one sanitizer.  25 medical kits comprising of oximeter and thermometer will be given to SHG members who are living within the community.  These kits to be used to monitor the spread of Covid infection.  Each SHG member to monitor to identify 20 individuals with covid symptoms and support in receiving timely treatment. 2500 individuals to receive face mask for protection</narrative>
  </description>
